# Python Engineering Standards

- Use full type hints everywhere.
- Use `| None` instead of `Optional`.
- Avoid `Any` unless it is truly necessary.
- Use Pydantic models or dataclasses for structured data.
- Keep functions small and single-responsibility.
- Avoid nesting deeper than two levels.
- Prefer early returns over nested conditions.
- Use explicit, descriptive names.
- Avoid generic names like `data`, `item`, and `obj`.
